                "description": {
                    "chat": "",
                    "unidentified": "",
                    "value": "<p>10 feet.</p>\n<p>An attic whisperer enshrouds itself in a tapestry of stolen voices. Each living creature that enters or starts their turn in the aura must succeed at a <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"19\" data-pf2-traits=\"auditory,aura,emotion,enchantment,mental,occult,concentrate\" data-pf2-label=\"Aura of Sobs DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span> save or the unnerving, bitter sobs render them distraught and they become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} for as long as they remain within the aura. A creature that succeeds is temporarily immune for 1 hour.</p>\n<p>The attic whisperer can activate or deactivate the aura with a single free action, which has the concentrate trait.</p>"
